%U A397852 5413033189858806621176717,790381745527568484809199216,97359148805931173323058612362,10363147478912326563725825779702,970975837820247575709416072754270
%N A397852 Number of finishing sequences of n darts in a game to score exactly 501 points.
%C A397852 A finishing sequence of n darts is a sequence of scoring sections (nothing, single 1 through 20, double 1 through 20, treble 1 through 20, outer bull, or inner bull) whose scores add up to exactly 501, and in which the last dart must hit a double scoring area (double 1 through 20 or inner bull).
%H A397852 Jianing Song, <a href="/A397852/b397852.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 9..1000</a>
%H A397852 Reddit, <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/askmath/comments/1pjfp5t/ten_dart_finish_combinations_from_501/">Ten dart finish combinations from 501</a>.
%H A397852 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nine-dart_finish">Nine-dart finish</a> (contains the a(9) = 3944 nine-dart finishing sequences).
%o A397852 (PARI) score = x*(1-x^20)/(1-x) + x^2*(1-x^40)/(1-x^2) + x^3*(1-x^60)/(1-x^3) + x^25 + x^50 + 1 \\ g.f. of dart scores
%o A397852 double_score = x^2*(1-x^40)/(1-x^2) + x^50 \\ g.f. of double scores
%o A397852 P(n) = lift(Mod(score,x^502)^(n-1)*double_score) \\ g.f. of scores <= 501 of n darts doubling-out
%o A397852 a(n) = polcoeff(P(n), 501)
%K A397852 nonn,new
%O A397852 9,1
%A A397852 _Jianing Song_, Jul 12 2026
